						<div class="postbody">It is not that noticeable or bad if pitch of the drum vary a bit.
<br />
<br />I don't think that fast pitch drop that is required for a drum could sound too melodic to create any problem for listener. Any real drums (rock drumkit, for example) has own tuning and need to be tuned just like any other musical instrument, but it does not create any problem, you'll never say that kick or snare (they are tuned as well) are 'melodic'.</div>

