					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In my music engine, all drums go through the sound effects engine. The kick drum in the opening to <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=84524#84524" class="postlink">Zap Ruder</a>, for example, is one sound effect played on the triangle channel and another sound effect on the noise channel. This way the drum sound naturally interrupts whatever's behind it.</div>

